    <item>
      <title>How to backup, offline, or archive a git repo</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/git/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Aug 2025 00:08:20 -0700</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/git/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m not sure why this isn&amp;rsquo;t really covered simply in one place but here it goes&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Using just the cli you can do the following:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;FYI: the &lt;code&gt;git archive&lt;/code&gt; command is not the thing we want, that is more for prepping code for deployment to a siteâ€¦&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;What we really want is to &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/archiving-a-github-repository/backing-up-a-repository&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;offline or backup the repo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The idea is:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;git clone --mirror &amp;lt;repository_url&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;which results in a dir &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;repository_url&amp;gt;.git/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;cd &amp;lt;repository_url&amp;gt;.git/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
